    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Adult habitus of Cobacella palmensis sp. n.; (A) adult male lateral view, (B) adult male dorsal view, (C) adult female lateral view, and (D) adult female dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391231/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391233>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Adult male of Cobacella palmensis sp. n.; (A) head, pronotum, and mesonotum in dorsal view, (B) lateral view, and (C) head and pronotum in frontal view; scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391233/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391239>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Male Cobacella palmensis sp. n. terminalia; (A) lateral view, (B) ventral view, and (C) dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391239/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391243>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Aedeagus of Cobacella palmensis sp. n.; (A) right lateral view, (B) left lateral view, (C) dorsal view, and (D) ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391243/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391249>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Maximum Likelihood trees (1,000 replicates) showing the relationship of Cobacella palmensis sp. n. relative to other available species of Otiocerinae; (A) COI, (B)18S, (C) 28S and (D) consensus tree based on concatenated COI and 18S sequence data, scale bar = percent nucleotide difference." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391249/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391261>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Habitus of a female Cobacella specimen from La Selva, Costa Rica (University of Delaware Insect Research Collection, UDCC), (A) lateral habitus view, (B) dorsal habitus view, (C) ventrofrontal view, and (D) label." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391261/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391257>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Habitus of Cobacella specimens from the Natural History Museum, London (BMNH); (A) Cobacella sexguttata Fennah (Amazonas, Brazil, Det. P.S. Broomfield), (B–C) Cobacella rubescens (Fowler), syntype female (B) lateral and (C) dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391257/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391259>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Habitus of Cobacella rubescens syntype female from Orizaba, Veracruz, Mexico (image credit Harald Bruckner, Hemiptera Image Collection, Natural History Museum Vienna); (A) lateral view, (B) dorsal view (C) ventral view, and (C) labels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391259/files/figure.png" ;
